race.description: Scone Equine Hospital Country Boosted Hcp (Bm58)
race.comment: QUICK SHARP (5) stalked the pace then went home a shade the better last start in a BM58 over 1100m at Armidale. Stretches out to this distance for the first time but it looks the right move. Getting up in the weights but won't spend a cent from the draw and can certainly get the job done again. MIRAI SAN (4) returned to form last start with a game second over this distance at Tamworth after racing right up near the pace from the outset. Lightly raced four-year-old who just needs luck slotting in from a wide gate to be in the finish again. VIERVILLE (2) resumes after a six-month break. Speedy gelding who has only won of soft or synthetic surfaces. Draws a nice gate and while fresh should give backers a sight. JOSEPHINE (12) strips fitter and gets out to a more suitable trip this time. SHEILA'S FANTA SEA (9) is another who will tighten up in condition following a sound return last time out.
